abstract: The California attorney general’s office has shut down 10 websites that mimicked state’s official health insurance marketplace.
snippet: The California attorney general’s office has shut down 10 websites that mimicked state’s official health insurance marketplace.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES—The California attorney general’s office has shut down 10 websites that mimicked state’s official health insurance marketplace, the attorney general, Kamala Harris, announced Wednesday.
headline_main: California Shuts Down Sites Mimicking State Insurance Marketplace

abstract: Two of the central players in the biggest settlement of the financial crisis were once on opposite sides of the negotiating table.
snippet: Two of the central players in the biggest settlement of the financial crisis were once on opposite sides of the negotiating table.
lead_paragraph: At the end of a conference call on the night of Oct. 18, JPMorgan Chase’s chief executive and the attorney general left their top lieutenants to hash out the details of a tentative $13 billion settlement. The talks, led Tony West, the associate attorney general at the Justice Department, and Stephen M. Cutler, JPMorgan’s general counsel, could still fall apart over how much wrongdoing the bank will admit on its questionable mortgage practices.
headline_main: Weekend Reading: 2 Key Players in JPMorgan’s $13 Billion Deal

abstract: The nonprofit, which has ties to the billionaire conservative businessmen Charles and David Koch, failed to disclose over $15 million in contributions it funneled into California referendum battles.
snippet: The nonprofit, which has ties to the billionaire conservative businessmen Charles and David Koch, failed to disclose over $15 million in contributions it funneled into California referendum battles.
lead_paragraph: A secretive nonprofit group with ties to the billionaire conservative businessmen Charles and David Koch admitted to improperly failing to disclose more than $15 million in contributions it funneled into state referendum battles in California, state officials there announced Thursday.

snippet: Forced out of office in August amid allegations of sexual harassment, Mr. Filner pleaded guilty to a charge of false imprisonment, among others.
lead_paragraph: SAN DIEGO — Bob Filner, the former San Diego mayor forced out of office in a storm of sexual harassment allegations, pleaded guilty on Tuesday to a series of false imprisonment and battery charges involving three women.

snippet: A fully renovated prewar duplex, with five bedrooms and a separate guest suite, features open city views to the north and east.
